This is Perl module Scalar::Lazy::Cached.

INSTALLATION

Type the following command:

    $ curl -L http://cpanmin.us | perl - Scalar::Lazy::Cached

Or install cpanm and then run the following command to install
Scalar::Lazy::Cached:

    $ cpanm Scalar::Lazy::Cached

If you get an archive of this distribution, unpack it and build it
as per the usual:

    $ tar xzf Scalar-Lazy-Cached-$version.tar.gz
    $ cd Scalar-Lazy-Cached-$version
    $ perl Makefile.PL
    $ make && make test

Then install it:

    $ make install

DOCUMENTATION

Scalar::Lazy::Cached documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    $ perldoc Scalar::Lazy::Cached

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

